============================================================
  MATHEMATICS
============================================================

Theorem/Law:  Bayes Theorem
Branch:       Probability
Formula:      P(H|E) = P(E|H)P(H)/P(E)
Applications: ML, spam filters, medical testing
Discoverer:   Thomas Bayes (1763)

Theorem/Law:  Central Limit Theorem
Branch:       Statistics
Formula:      Sample means approach normal distribution
Applications: Polling, quality control, finance
Discoverer:   Lyapunov (1901)

Theorem/Law:  Taylor Series
Branch:       Calculus
Formula:      f(x) = sum of f^n(a)/n! * (x-a)^n
Applications: Numerical computation, signal processing
Discoverer:   Brook Taylor (1715)

============================================================
  PHILOSOPHY
============================================================

Concept:      Virtue Ethics
Branch:       Ethics
Definition:   Ethics is about developing virtuous character traits
Philosopher:  Aristotle
Example:      A courageous person acts courageously habitually; ethics is becoming good

Concept:      Existentialism
Branch:       Metaphysics
Definition:   Existence precedes essence; radical freedom and responsibility
Philosopher:  Jean-Paul Sartre
Example:      You are not born kind or cruel; you become so through choices

Concept:      Determinism
Branch:       Metaphysics
Definition:   All events are causally determined by prior events and natural laws
Philosopher:  Laplace/Spinoza
Example:      If universe were rewound exactly, every event would repeat identically

============================================================
  QUESTION & ANSWER PAIRS
============================================================

Q1: What is inflation?
A1: Inflation is the general rise in price levels over
     time, reducing purchasing power. Caused by excess money
     supply, high demand, or supply shocks. Measured by the
     Consumer Price Index.

Q2: What is a neuron?
A2: A neuron is a nerve cell that processes and transmits
     information through electrical and chemical signals.
     Key parts: dendrites (receive signals), cell body, axon
     (send signals).

Q3: What is evolution?
A3: Evolution by natural selection: organisms with
     beneficial traits reproduce more, passing traits to
     offspring. Over generations, populations change. Darwin
     proposed this in 1859.

Q4: What is the internet?
A4: The internet is a global network of interconnected
     computers using TCP/IP protocols. It began as ARPANET
     in 1969 and became public with the World Wide Web in
     1994.

Q5: What is metabolism?
A5: Metabolism is all chemical reactions in an organism
     that maintain life: catabolism (breaking molecules for
     energy) and anabolism (building complex molecules from
     simple ones).

